Having little to do with REST but my strong preference is:

	/yyyy/mm/dd

Instead of:

	/yyyy-mm-dd

Because the former is hackable and the latter is not:

	/yyyy/mm/
	/yyyy/

This also allows for relative references in content returned as per specs.
So a link to &quot;/yyyy/mm/foo/&quot; could be referred to simply as &quot;foo/&quot; in the
representation returned by &quot;/yyyy/mm/&quot;.

